The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Big win for Khalsa Blues

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Khalsa Blues and Calcutta Police registered contrasting wins in their opening round matches of the 110th Indian Oil All India Beighton Cup hockey tournament on Tuesday. 

While Khalsa Blues blanked Howrah Hockey Training Centre 3-0, Calcutta Police had to break a lot of sweat before edging CC amp;FC Gremlins 2-1 at CC amp;FC on the inaugural day. 

The one-sided affair at the Mohammedan Sporting ground saw Khalsa Blues take the lead in the 18 th minute through P. Paswan and the lead was enhanced by Yakub Sangma and the rout was complete when Gurmeet Singh made a clinical finish to seal the fate of the match. 

At the CC amp;FC ground, the hosts took the lad with P. Shah finding the mark. 

The policemen restored parity through Preetam Mistr.followed by S. Panda, who struck the winner. 




